title: Metadata Analyst
description: Performed as a Senior Analyst, responsible for analyzing, identifying, tracking, and reporting new and unusual entities in support of US PACOM and national consumer requirements. Provided metadata analysis support to consumers worldwide and to intelligence offices within NSA/CSS-H, which include India, Pakistan, and most notably the Counter-Terrorism office. As a metadata analyst I responded to request for services (RFS) in the discovering of target communication methods and reported findings to national consumers. Aided in the initial SIGINT development in the India/Pakistan office. I also conducted a 90-day network survey identifying new sources of foreign intelligence for future tasking and exploitation. Discovered 66 suspected terrorists who were allegedly involved in the attacks in Mumbai. I have trained over 50 personnel deploying to Iraq, Afghanistan, and the Philippines.

title: Geo-Spatial Metadata Analyst (GMA)
description: Served as a GMA Subject Matter Expert (SME) supporting OIF. As a GMA I was responsible for the research and analysis of multiple intelligence sources aiding in the identification, development, tracking, and timely reporting of High-Value Targets (HVT) in two distinct areas of operation (AO). I also presented intelligence products in the form of target packages and briefings displaying pattern of life analysis, link analysis, target capabilities and vulnerabilities, and predictive analysis to recommend target pursuit to combatant commanders and civilian officials. Through my initiative and extensive research efforts I was able to gain intimate knowledge of HVT’s and the AO which I was assigned. The knowledge gained allowed me to plan, coordinate, and synthesize research to produce all-source intelligence products/responses. As a result of my target analysis efforts I authored nine target packages that directly contributed to the apprehension or death of 26 known insurgents, seven HVT’s and a 90% hold rate for detainees. Also, while in support of SIGINT driven missions I made time to identify process improvements, develop new training plans, and to conduct training in the use of National Intelligence Databases and advanced analytical techniques. In addition, I responded to over 35 requests for information from tactical consumers producing high quality intelligence products to satisfy mission demands. Lastly, prior to my departure I coordinated with replacement analysts to ensure a seamless transition and the continuity of mission efforts.
